The paper discusses model checking techniques for interval temporal logics, which are used to reason about temporal properties that cannot be expressed by point-based temporal logics. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of modal logic, which is often used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) research. The paper also discusses the complexity of the problem in different system models, which could fall under the Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper focuses on the application of model checking to software engineering (cs.SE), which is another possible sub-category.
